Argentina President, Alberto Fernandez, has leased Lionel Messi’s private jet for four days. According to Marca, Fernandez leased the jet for $160,000 for his official visit to Mexico to celebrate the 200th anniversary of the country’s independence. Messi’s jet became an option because of its coronavirus preventive requirement.
.
Messi bought his Gulfstream V plane for #15m in 2018. Meanwhile, DAILY POST reported earlier that Portuguese and Juventus superstar, Cristiano Ronaldo recently flew his pet, Pepe on his private jet to Madrid to continue its rehabilitation after it was ran over by a car in Turin.